  "prompt": "How can I get a OBC NCL Certificate?",
  "response": "To obtain an OBC (Other Backward Class) Non-Creamy Layer (NCL) Certificate, follow these steps:\n\n1. Eligibility:\n- Must belong to an OBC category\n- Family income should be below the prescribed limit\n- Not belong to the creamy layer\n\n2. Required Documents:\n- Proof of identity (Aadhaar card, voter ID)\n- Caste certificate\n- Family income certificate\n- Residence proof\n- Recent passport-sized photographs\n- Parents' income documents\n\n3. Process:\na) Offline Method:\n- Visit Tahsildar/Revenue Officer's office\n- Submit application with required documents\n- Pay prescribed fees\n- Receive certificate after verification\n\nb) Online Method:\n- Visit state government's official website\n- Fill online application form\n- Upload necessary documents\n- Pay application fee\n- Track application status\n\n4. Important Points:\n- Certificate is valid for one year\n- Income limit changes periodically\n- Check state-specific guidelines\n- Renewal required after expiry\n\n5. Verification:\n- Certificate will be verified by concerned authorities\n- Additional documents might be requested\n\nTip: Contact local revenue office or check state government website for specific details and updated procedures.",
